        <td>9 a.m.–9 p.m.</td> 
       </tr> 
       <tr> 
        <td>Sunday</td> 
        <td>9 a.m.–midnight</td> 
       </tr> 
      </tbody> 
      <tbody> 
       <tr> 
        <td colspan="2">(Hours subject to change)</td> 
       </tr> 
      </tbody> 
     </table> 
     <h4>Our indoor facilities include:</h4> 
     <ul> 
      <li>A fitness center with a weight room.</li> 
      <li>A large cardiovascular training area.</li> 
      <li>Four racquetball and one squash court.</li> 
      <li>Three large multi-use rooms.</li> 
      <li>Four full size multi-use basketball courts.</li> 
     </ul> 
     <ul class="striped alt2"> 
      <li><strong>Intramurals</strong><br> <span class="xpander">Over 7,500 students, staff and faculty annually participate in intramurals at UC Riverside. The program offers more than a dozen sports, including: 
        <ul class="tight"> 
         <li>Basketball</li> 
         <li>Flag football</li> 
         <li>Indoor soccer</li> 
         <li>Volleyball</li> 
         <li>Softball</li> 
         <li>Dodge ball</li> 
         <li>Bowling</li> 
         <li>Badminton</li> 
         <li>Table tennis</li> 
         <li>Tennis</li> 
         <li>Racquetball</li> 
        </ul> To sign up for intramurals contact the Intramural Office at (951) 827-7039 or email us at <a href="mailto:competitivesports@ucr.edu">CompetitiveSports@ucr.edu</a>. Already in a league? Check out our <a href="http://www.imsports.ucr.edu/">results and statistics pages</a>. </span></li> 
      <li><strong>Outdoor Excursions</strong><br> <span class="xpander">For over 20 years, UCR <a href="http://excursions.ucr.edu/">Outdoor Excursions</a> has been serving the community with a variety of programs and services that emphasize skill development, environmental awareness and community, the outings and rental programs are open to UCR students and community members 18-years and older. Outings include: 
        <ul class="tight"> 
         <li>Rock climbing</li> 
         <li>Kayaking</li> 
         <li>Hiking</li> 
         <li>Snow boarding</li> 
         <li>Snowshoeing</li> 
         <li>Snow camping</li> 
         <li>Backpacking</li> 
         <li>Team building</li> 
         <li>Surfing</li> 
         <li>Canyoneering</li> 
         <li>Caving</li> 
         <li>Snorkeling</li> 
         <li>Scuba</li> 
        </ul> We also offer <a href="http://recreation.ucr.edu/outdoor_excursions/wildernesstrips/Pages/CustomExcursions.aspx">custom excursions</a>, outdoor leader development, team excursions, youth excursions, <a href="http://recreation.ucr.edu/outdoor_excursions/climbingwall/Pages/ClimbingWall.aspx">a rock wall and ropes course</a> and a fully stocked <a href="http://recreation.ucr.edu/outdoor_excursions/equipmentrentals/Pages/AvailableGear.aspx">rental shop</a>. Contact us at (951) 827-7040 or e-mail us at <a href="mailto:oe@ucr.edu">oe@ucr.edu</a>. </span></li> 
      <li><strong>Recreation Classes</strong><br> <span class="xpander">Want to get fit in an aerobics class? Learn yoga? Take a basic self defense course? How about learn to play the bagpipes? These are just a few of the dozens of classes offered through the <a href="http://recreation.ucr.edu/schedules/Pages/RecreationClassSchedule.aspx">Recreation Activity Instructional Classes</a>. These non-credit courses are designed to teach skills that an individual can use during his or her leisure time and are taught by qualified instructors who have special skills they wish to share. Course fees cover instructor’s salary and most supplies. </span></li> 
      <li><strong>Club Sports</strong><br> <span class="xpander">The <a href="http://recreation.ucr.edu/competitiveSports/Pages/SportsClubs.aspx">Sport Club Program</a> is an exciting alternative to Intramural Sports. Both recreational and competitive clubs are available for students, faculty, and staff. UCR Clubs are a great way of socializing and meeting others who share the same interests, or as a means of getting involved in an activity with a competitive team. Sports sponsored include: 
        <ul class="tight"> 
         <li>Rugby</li> 
         <li>Men’s soccer</li> 
         <li>Women's soccer </li> 
         <li>Ultimate frisbee</li> 
         <li>Badminton</li> 
         <li>Tae Kwon Do</li> 
        </ul> New club sports are always welcome. Contact Kevin Martin (<a href="mailto:kevin.martin@ucr.edu">kevin.martin@ucr.edu</a>) at (951) 827-4465 for information on how to start a new club team. </span></li> 
      <li><strong>Health and Fitness</strong><br> <span class="xpander">The center offers an extensive weight room and cardio facilities. Or get fit faster through the <a href="http://recreation.ucr.edu/fitness_wellness/Pages/PersonalTraining.aspx">Personal Training Program</a>. </span></li> 
     </ul> 
    </div> 
